131000000.text:
Jimmy Ace, Jimmy Ace is my name.
Oh, you're my barren heart's only flame.

131000002.text:
What?
What's that tewwible racket, meow?!

131000003.text:
Come and join my hearty band!
We are the hunters of this land!

131000004.text:
Let's fish out the treasure of our life here!
Let's find the Hesuth with Jimmy Ace, my dear!

131000005.text:
Graah! That song makes me fur-ious! 
Let's just get the Hesuth ourselves, meow!

131000006.text:
Who the heck caught the Beach Turtle?
I wanted to catch it first to get the master's approval!

131000007.text: What, mrrow? Why are you grumbling?

131000008.text:
I've been looking for the Hesuth that appears around here...
But it won't show up no matter how many traps I set.

131000009.text:
We made a bet to see who can catch it first...
I'm going to go broke at this rate!

131000010.text:
Trapping takes real skill, meow!
If you can't even manage that, you don't deserve to catch a Hesuth!

131000011.text:
What? Why, you little!
I'd like to see if you can catch one!

131000012.text: Ha, you're going to regret saying that, hiss!

131000013.text: I'm pretty sure the Hesuth here is the easiest to handle.

131000015.text:
Ah, why did you have to shout so suddenly?
You almost scared the wits out of me.

131000016.text: Are you looking for the Hesuth?

131000017.text:
Oh! Yes, you're right.
Actually, I was kind of scared of even finding one, since I'm not sure if I can take it down by myself.

131000018.text:
If someone else takes care of the Hesuth, you won't even have to look for it, right?
We'll help you, mrrow!

131000019.text:
You mean it?
In that case, I could just tell my master that someone already handled it before me.

131000020.text: You can count on us, meow!

131000021.text:
Duchi... I'm in a good mood today!
Ooh! Duchi... You're Jimmy Ace's friend!

131000024.text:
What's up with that guy?
Is it possible for a Ploggle to befweind a person, meow?

131000025.text:
Duchi! Looking for the Hesuth, the Hesuth!
Let's find this world's treasure, to the west, to the east!

131000026.text:
Grah! That's tewwible singing!
Let's just catch the Hesuth ourselves, meow!

131000027.text: Aw... The master doesn't look for me at all these days.

131000028.text:
This is my chance to catch this region's Hesuth once and for all!
Too bad I didn't learn how to windwalk. Dang it.

131000030.text:
I managed to locate the Hesuth, but it's on the other side of the bridge.
I can't get myself to cross it at all!

131000031.text:
Leave it to us, meow!
We'll be back faster than you can shake a tail, haha!

131000032.text: I'm terrified of Gnarloxes. What should I do?

131000033.text:
Excuse me!
Would you be able to lend me a hand, if you're not too busy?

131000035.text:
I was foolishly bold enough to tell the master that I'd vanquish the Hesuth in this area,
but I'm so terrified that I can barely take another step.

131000036.text: Would you be able to take down the Hesuth on my behalf?

131000037.text: Ha! That's a piece of cake, mrrow!

131000038.text:
Well, we do have quite a ways to go. 
But we can finish this in no time, so why not!

131000039.text: Duchi... Our days ahead may be long and weary!

131000040.text: But as long as we're together, no Hesuth can scare me!

131000042.text: Grah! Who's singing again so terribly?!

131000043.text:
We'd better get rid of all these Hesuths so they'll stop singing!
Let's teach them not to mess with us, meow!

131000044.text:
It seems like there's a hideout near the Daybreak Camp...
I wonder if there's a way to investigate discreetly.

131000046.text:
You look like you enjoy going on adventures.
In that case, I'm sure you've heard of the Daybreak, right?

131000047.text:
I've come across intel that they have a secret hideout in their camp.
Who knows what sort of nefarious schemes they're plotting in there.

131000048.text:
We can't let them do that, meow!
We'll find that hideout!

131000049.text: Thanks. Please go find and clear out their hideout.

131000050.text:
Ooh, if it isn't the new recruit!
All right, I'll give you a chance!

131000051.text: What? Don't you mean that you'll give them "our chance?"

131000052.text: No! We worked hard for it!

131000054.text:
It must be an act of providence that we met. So, I'll give you
this special chance to find and hunt this Hesuth.

131000055.text:
Say, you're really grateful for my generosity, aren't you? Haha!
All right, then off you go to find the Hesuth!

131000056.text:
Recruits! How did you know I was on a Hesuth hunt?
So, you want to enter the harsh world of Hesuth hunting, eh? Haha!

131000057.text: Cap, are you accepting the recruit? Are you going to give them another chance?

131000058.text: No, don't! This Hesuth is a seriously terrifying mutant!

131000059.text: (I guess I've entered the world of Hesuth hunting now...?)

131000060.text:
Krunchi, Munchi. This recruit is getting better all the time. They might even outshine us one day.
But we'll be the one to finish it. Eventually.

131000061.text:
Recruit, go find the Hesuth.
Even if we don't get there in time, I'm sure you can handle it on your own.

131000062.text:
Recruit, it's you again! Ugh, Recruit, you...
I gave you many chances and you keep ruining our plan.

131000063.text: He's right. You keep coming back alive, ruining our plan to fish in troubled water—

131000064.text: Be quiet! The Recruit can hear you!

131000065.text: (I hunted that Hesuth. What sort of plan did I ruin?)

131000066.text:
Tsk, tsk. You have no idea, do you? Of course, you're too naive to understand my grand plan.
Well, you'll just have to see it for yourself.

131000067.text:
I, the generous Jimmy Ace, will give you another chance, Recruit.
Find and fight a Hesuth. I'll see how good you are, then. Haha!

131000068.text:
You're the toughest recruit I've ever met.
You're there every time we find a Hesuth. This can't be a coincidence.

131000069.text: Err? Cap, are you going to give them a chance again?

131000070.text: Come on, don't! They'll beat it and leave again!

131000071.text: (It really can't be a coincidence that we keep running into each other.)

131000072.text:
Krunchi, Munchi. I know how hard you've worked for this.
Everyone in the expedition has, searching day and night to find this Hesuth.

131000073.text:
Now, why don't we give it to the recruit, so they can prove their worth at the risk of their life?
Show us what you've got. We might let you join us afterward. Haha!

131000074.text:
Haha! We meet again. All right, I acknowledge your mettle.
And I'll also accept you into my expedition team.

131000075.text: Cap! You can't accept new members before an important Hesuth hunt.

131000076.text: The hunts haven't been easy, and we can barely make a living as it is.

131000078.text:
Shut it! We can't make our living because of you.
We need new blood!

131000079.text:
Now, Recruit, I have faith in you.
Find a Hesuth and prove yourself.

131000080.text:
Warrior, have you seen Jimmy Ace the Hesuth Hunter...
Oh, it's the recruit.

131000081.text:
It is. We had to move to this Taero Forest because of you.
Did you follow us to interfere with us again?

131000082.text: (What are they talking about? They think I followed them?)

131000083.text:
Anyways, now that you're here, you should help find Cap.
He went to find a Hesuth and hasn't returned.

131000084.text:
Yes. Jimmy Ace gave you a lot of opportunities in the Sapphire Basin.
It's time you repay him!

131000085.text:
Look around for a Hesuth and Cap.
We'll be looking, too.

131000086.text:
Recruit! It's you!
Did you search the Cobweb Forest Trail?

131000087.text:
Jimmy Ace can't have been killed by the Hesuth, can he?
You didn't find any human bones nearby, did you?

131000089.text:
Munchi, what are you talking about?
There's no way Cap would go down so easily!

131000090.text:
I-I don't know! I don't like this place!
There's a Hesuth around here, too. What if it comes for us?

131000091.text:
We have to find him, no matter what.
Recruit, look for Hesuth traces around here. Perhaps Cap is somewhere nearby.

131000092.text:
Recruit! Did you find Cap?
...Wait, you're alone. Didn't you see him at all?

131000093.text:
You're a good hunter. Are you sure you tried your best to find him?
Krunchi, we tried. We should just let Cap go...

131000094.text: (Did something really happen to Jimmy Ace?)

131000095.text:
Munchi, stop being so weak!
Jimmy Ace is our captain. He's Cap! There's no way he could die so easily!

131000096.text:
But Krunchi, you know his hunting skills aren't exactly... Ahem.
At any rate, this place is really dangerous. Any one of us could die here.

131000097.text:
Munchi, you need a good beating, don't cha?
Recruit, there's another Hesuth around here. Go look for it and Cap.
In the meantime... Munchi, we need to talk.

131000098.text:
R-Recruit! How did you know I was here?
Ahem, did you find Jimmy Ace?

131000099.text:
You didn't find him, did you? I knew it!
How can you? He either ran away or died.

131000101.text:
Gah, I came this far for nothing. Now, how can I get back?
...Oh yeah, there's the recruit!

131000102.text:
Ahem, Recruit. Let me tell you something that only I know.
There's an incredible Hesuth around here. Surprised to hear that?

131000103.text:
Hunt that Hesuth, and we'll rake in the money!
We can even use the cash to form a new Hesuth expedition team. I'll be in charge of the info, and you take care of the hunting. What do you say?

131000104.text:
Munchi, we'll have a word later. Ugh...
Recruit, welcome! Someone saw Cap around here.

131000105.text:
But after that... You know,
honestly no one can hunt Hesuths in such a dangerous place.

131000106.text: (I probably shouldn't tell Krunchi about the new expedition team.)

131000107.text:
Munchi, stop talking nonsense.
Recruit, see the traces of a Hesuth in front of us? Someone saw Cap examining them.

131000108.text:
But I've heard the rumors!
The Hesuth that shows up here isn't normal for some reason. It's very dangerous!

131000109.text:
But we can't give up on Cap.
Recruit, please. Our future in the Hesuth hunting expedition rests on your shoulders!

131000110.text:
Ooh, if it isn't the new recruit!
Welcome. You've never hunted Hesuths in Caelite Land before, have you?

131000111.text:
Ah, I can see you trembling. Relax.
It's not difficult to hunt Hesuths. Just find and hunt them, that's all.

131000113.text:
Hey, lower your head!
Do you know who he is? He's the fabled Jimmy Ace of the Sapphire Basin!

131000114.text:
Haha! That's right, I'm that Jimmy Ace.
You're lucky, Recruit. Now that you've met me, you'll never have to worry about money or getting a job!

131000115.text:
Haha! Now, find and hunt a Hesuth around here.
I don't always give away a chance as special as this!

131000116.text: Haha! The Hesuth has to have finished the recruit by now.

131000117.text: Jimmy Ace... The recruit is still alive...

131000118.text:
What? What the...? Why are you still alive? You even hunted the Hesuth.
You're a tough cookie, aren't you?

131000120.text:
Haha! It's you. You're that recruit!
You've survived and followed me all the way to Caelite Land!

131000121.text:
All right, then I'd better prepare a perfect Hesuth for you.
We'll meet again. Haha!

131000123.text:
You're alive!
Thank the gods, we were able to meet again!

131000125.text: Munchi left me and ran away to the Sapphire Basin!

131000126.text:
We promised the people of this place that we'd hunt Hesuths for them.
Munchi ran away with the money we got from them!

131000127.text:
In case you haven't noticed, I can't hunt Hesuths.
But you can, can't you? Recruit, please help me. I can't pay these people back!

131000129.text:
While you went to hunt a Hesuth, the people brought me here.
They want me to take care of their Hesuths as soon as possible.

131000130.text: (Jimmy Ace is definitely somewhere in the Caelite Land.)

131000131.text:
But the gods didn't forsake me completely.
They sent you here!

131000132.text:
Can you believe there's a dangerous Hesuth in such a beautiful place?
Be careful.

131000133.text: ...Why are you still standing there? You're going to help me, right?

131000134.text: Recruit, you've managed to get this far!

131000135.text:
I wish you haven't.
There's a really terrifying Hesuth in front of us.

131000137.text:
Chuah, don't.
This recruit is a fearless and capable hunter.

131000138.text:
I told you I'd prepare a perfect Hesuth for you, remember?
Now, go follow its traces and fight it!

131000139.text:
Say, you're so grateful for my generosity, aren't you?
Haha!

131000141.text:
Krunchi? Is that you?
You're alive!

131000142.text:
I knew we'd meet again!
I've never given up on you!

131000143.text:
Have you been looking for me all this time?
Krunchi, don't ever leave me again!

131000144.text: Jimmy Ace... should I treat him like an older brother?

131000145.text:
Haha! Chuah, no need to be so polite.
Krunchi is my right-hand man. Actually, he's family. Haha!

131000146.text:
Recruit! You're so shameless, showing up again like this!
You ran away from the Iron Claw last time!

131000147.text:
Cap, don't say that.
The Recruit has been helping me since we were in Taero Forest.

131000149.text: Not bad. Looks can be deceiving, I guess.

131000150.text:
Watch your mouth.
The Recruit is one of us!

131000151.text:
Krunchi, you're right. I did acknowledge the Recruit already.
Speaking of which, Recruit, I want you to help Krunchi.

131000152.text:
Krunchi has found out there's a Hesuth around here.
Recruit, go take care of it like the good hunter you are!

131000154.text: (I never thought that the saltwater hunters would be here...)

131000155.text: You. How did you get here? \n Ji-geun Woo! You said no one could come here?

131000157.text: Have you ever…\n did you sell my name? Kah ha, ha ha ha!

131000158.text: Khahaha! I think a newcomer has followed us~\nWould you like a newcomer to join us?

131000159.text: You can't leave this job to anyone.

131000160.text: Why are you so stiff? \nYou know the skills of a rookie!

131000161.text: Stop it! I am the captain.

131000162.text: The skills of a newcomer aren't bad. They have the guts. \nSo, I'll leave this seawater hunting to the newcomers.

131000163.text: … chi… the life of a seawater must not be lost. \nYou must be alive.

131000164.text: It's weak, but it's hidden. I'll take care of \nHaesu.

131000166.text: Good job, newbie. \nWe'll go find another Haesu. Let's meet again.

131000167.text: You did a great job! Let's meet again!

131000168.text: (Woo Ji-geun seems to care quite a bit...)

131000169.text: Rookie, I've been waiting. \nThen shall we start hunting?

131000172.text: Will you do well this time too? \nI believe!

131000173.text: You must not completely end the life of seawater.

131000174.text: You, didn't you see what the newbie did last time? \nStop making a mess!

131000175.text: Captain! The newcomer did a good job!

131000176.text: The seawater is barely alive.\nIt was very dangerous.

131000177.text: Hmm… Ji-geun Woo, it seems different from what you thought?

131000178.text: We'll go find another seawater, so wait for Odo-dok's call.

131000179.text: (I think I'll be contacting you soon!)

131000180.text: Rookie! You're here! \n You came alone, aren't you?

131000181.text: Captain, I think it's right that you came alone. \n I can't even see Woo Ji-geun around.

131000183.text: Rookie, listen carefully. \n This hunting will be conducted by ourselves.

131000184.text: Captain, shouldn’t we properly inform the newcomers as well?

131000185.text: If you keep gathering, you'll be exposed. \n Let's get together again after defeating Haesu.

131000193.text: Rookie! Didn't you know? \nWoo Ji-geun was one with the Black Dawn!

131000194.text: Woo Ji-geun has always been aiming for the sea water of the Haeryong Mountains.

131000195.text: So the captain! \nWoo Ji-geun must never be allowed to take seawater!

131000196.text: Of course! It's not going to go the way he wants it to. \nRookie! Get rid of them before Ji-geun Woo and the Black Dawn get their seawater!

131000198.text: Did you really notice? \n Those idiots? So quickly?

131000199.text: Things aren't good.\nYou'd better not disappoint me any more.

131000200.text: Rookie! Haven't you met Woo Ji-geun?

131000201.text: We didn't have much of a problem. There's no one to follow us if we run away.

131000202.text: (Is there no choice but to admit that?)

131000203.text: Now then, shall we talk about business or hunting?

131000204.text: There's seawater around here too! He's very strong!

131000205.text: Perhaps Ji-geun Woo is also looking for that seawater.

131000206.text: Come on, let's go and show the skills of a seawater hunter!

131000207.text: Maybe Woo Ji-geun will come here? \n It will be a very interesting sight!

131000208.text: Hey! It can't be like this! Why do you keep getting late one step at a time?

131000213.text: newcomer! you met well \nWhat do you do, Captain?

131000215.text: I don't know either! Is it because he sees Ji-geun Woo doing his best with a single knife, or is it because there are a lot of really strong hunters around?

131000216.text: Yes, newbie! You go ahead and set up the captain's flag.

131000217.text: Even the hunters here say that there is seawater that is difficult to deal with.\nI roughly figured out the location, so let's go!

131000218.text: ...what were you doing? Hurry before the others catch you!

131000219.text: ha ha ha! Newbie, well done. Well done!

131000221.text: Oh Dodok! who am i That's the great harvest god! \nI mean, it was all part of a grand plan!

131000222.text: yes? What do you mean, boss?

131000223.text: After all, if you don't tell me with my own mouth, I can't understand it with your narrow insight.\nDidn't the public recruitment only attract chaffs who don't really matter?

131000225.text: ha ha ha ha newcomer. You are truly a true country!\nNow, please accept me as a member of our expedition! ha ha ha ha

131000226.text: No, no! Now you are my left arm!

131000227.text: Hey, you've come a long way! Congratulations, newbie! \nYou know it's all thanks to me, right?

131000228.text: This is not the time to be like this, Odo-dok.\nLet's go tell the news that we defeated the seawater!

131000229.text: newcomer! No, no! Our left arm is here!

131000230.text: Come on, I don't have time for this. It's out right away!

131000232.text: There are rumors that Harvest God killed the seawater, so there are a lot of jobs!\nThe pay is great...Oops!

131000233.text: ruler! Quiet, Quiet! Don't be silly!\nHow can you ignore those who are suffering from seawater?

131000234.text: It's time for us to go!\nGo, left arm! Ha ha ha ha ha!

131000235.text: ha ha ha ha! It's also my left arm!

131000236.text: (...how it is said that thanksgiving seems to be the harvest cap)

131000237.text: You are saying it for granted.\nYou are my left arm, so what you did is the same as what I did.

131000238.text: Besides, this level of seawater is not at the level that I, the great Harvester God, can do.\nMy left arm, you are just right.

131000239.text: Well then, we'll go find another seawater, so wait for Odo-dok's call.

131000240.text: Don't procrastinate like last time, just jump right in!

131000241.text: I don't know where he rolled, but this is my territory. \nGet off when you say nice things!

131000242.text: Where's the zone for seawater hunting?\nThe one who finds and kills first is the owner!

131000243.text: Oh hey, that's how it turns out, isn't it?

131000244.text: great. I'll give you a piece of particularly valuable seawater information.\nShow me your skills.

131000245.text: big haha Are you testing me?\nBut what about this? Before my left or right arm loses, I won't go out.

131000246.text: left arm! Come on! Let's take that challenge!

131000247.text: Well, do whatever you feel comfortable with~ \nLet's see how long we can shout.

131000248.text: Oh my left arm! You're back safely!\nIt's also my left arm! ha ha ha ha

131000249.text: Oh, I guess it wasn't an exaggerated rumor.

131000250.text: big haha My left arm's skills are like this, so you'll know my skills even if I don't tell you?

131000251.text: Sheesh. You're arguing about what you've only dealt with!\nIf you talk like that, you'll end up screaming and dying in no time?

131000252.text: Are you worried about me now?

131000253.text: what nonsense If you've treated seawater, get out of here.

131000255.text: Leader! Calm down!\nWhat do you do if you don't get paid?!

131000257.text: Leader! My left arm is here!\nWhat should I do now?

131000259.text: We need to take our pay off and catch the one who splattered!

131000260.text: of course! Of course you should catch it.

131000261.text: Audacity to deceive this great harvest hat! Propulsion without hesitation! \nA dark beauty like a red cherry! A talent not to be missed!

131000262.text: Leader? What do you mean, boss?!

131000263.text: left arm! Get rid of the seawater here faster than Shashak!\nShow your left arm skills so that Shashak wants to join our expedition!

131000264.text: The left arm of the harvest hat is you! Did you destroy my seawater?

131000266.text: The famous seawater that eats even the screams of this canyon?

131000268.text: You guys...were they were bigger than you thought?\nAnd very... Hoho. They're also very nice guys.

131000269.text: So, join our expedition team!\nThis is not an opportunity given to anyone!

131000270.text: Hmm~~ You mean you want to hire me?

131000271.text: right! Meeting like this is a relationship, especially Hani! Very~ Special!\nI'll give you a chance to go seawater hunting with us~

131000272.text: good! Instead, I'll check my skills one more time.\nI'll call you so please wait.

131000273.text: Leader! You didn't get paid this time, did you?

131000274.text: We're going to be a family soon, so what worries you! Hahahaha\nThat prudence that doesn't trust people easily! It's also a talent, it's a talent!

131000275.text: you came Left arm!\nThis is where Shashak found a new seawater.

131000276.text: Are you saying you can do it with your left arm again...?\nRight arm, harvest hat. Are you really strong?

131000277.text: It is unbearable to doubt the great Harvest God!

131000278.text: I know~ I know \nLeft arm Then, try again this time. Because he's very expensive.

131000279.text: Are you thorough in your calculations? big hahaha \nI really like you.

131000280.text: I like you too~\n...I've never seen fools so easy to deal with.

131000281.text: What did you just say?! dummy?

131000282.text: When did I? Right arm, you must have heard it wrong.\nLeft arm! Don't procrastinate, go ahead!

131000283.text: yes yes left arm! Go ahead and show us the skills of our expedition!

131000285.text: Dare... to deceive this body again...\nYou're a really great talent... Ha ha ha... Ha ha ha ha ha!!!!

131000286.text: Leader!! Calm down! We've been scammed, scam! \nThat's a whopping 3 times!

131000287.text: Ha ha ha... ha ha ha ha!

136000000.text: Not every harbor is the same.

136000001.text:
This place is bustling with seasoned sailors
and large vessels, carrying goods from all across the world.

136000002.text:
A transportation and trading hub that connects the Moonwater Plains to Haewol.
What's the name of this harbor again?

136000004.text:
The people of the Sapphire Basin suffered due to the Fissure,
but not as badly as the Ploggles.

136000005.text: Their village was burned to the ground, and the surrounding environment became contaminated.

136000006.text: This place, where their village once stood, is now swarming with the Consumed.

136000007.text: The Ploggles will never be able to return home so long as the they remain.

136000008.text: Is this your first time to the New Fishbelly Pub?

136000009.text:
The tragedy was appalling, but the people here
were resilient enough to rebuild this place into what it is now.

136000010.text:
This building, combining new and old construction styles,
symbolizes rebirth, the continuation of traditions, and newfound prosperity.

136000011.text:
Excuse me, over there! Please don't climb on the roof. It's dangerous. 
Wah! Don't run up and down the stairs!

136000012.text: You can't come in here! This place is extremely dangerous.

136000013.text: Not only because of those Hollows over there, but it's still susceptible to Fissures.

136000014.text:
It's hard to imagine now,
but this is where the old Fishbelly Pub, the center of the Sapphire Basin, used to stand.

136000015.text: I was told pure water used to flow here. Now, all I see is the dark, cracked earth.

136000016.text: The Fissure took many things away from us, but we shouldn't just sit down and cry.

136000017.text:
We must protect what we have left. 
Do you know who's terrorizing the wild animals and the Nature Society the most at this moment?

136000018.text:
It's warm-blooded people, not those scary-looking Hollows. 
Can you believe that? People!

136000019.text: If I see the Poacher Gang, I'm going to kill—I mean, teach them a lesson!

136000030.text: Welcome to Haewol. It must have been a tiring journey.

136000031.text:
Dojung Port was named so in honor of the first expedition
leader and has played a central role in pioneering and exploration ever since.

136000032.text: With the opening of additional docking facilities, we were able to increase production and traffic significantly.

136000033.text: The future is bright at Dojung Port! I hope I can sail with you all soon.

136000034.text: You can see the surrounding sea of Dojung Port from here.

136000035.text: Many explorers were attacked in the past. Not to mention all the smuggling and illegal entries...

136000036.text: This watchtower was built to prevent that... but after the area was stabilized, it was abandoned.

136000037.text: Strange individuals clad in black clothing started gathering recently.

136000038.text: Sigh. We should have just burned it to the ground...

136000039.text: Many people fell victim to monsters and diseases during the founding stage of Shadowed Mistwood.

136000040.text: This was a great tragedy to all explorers, including the Sol Seekers. We couldn't even give them a proper burial.

136000041.text: All we could do was find a patch of solid earth and lay them to rest in a mass grave...

136000042.text: We should... take a moment of silence for the souls of the deceased.

136000043.text: Let me warn you though, this place isn't safe.

136000044.text: The Sol Seekers are doing all they can, but with more outsiders coming in, crime is on the rise.

136000045.text: We hope you have a pleasant stay here and that you avoid the dangerous areas.

136000046.text: I heard Ape King Ogong comes by that large tree to duel from time to time...

136000047.text: You would love to take a closer look, right? Don't!

136000048.text: The Tranquil Woods is a peculiar place.

136000049.text: The boulders around the area create echoes which add to its mysterious atmosphere.

136000050.text: As you focus on the sound of water, you start to feel the flow of the wind against your skin.

136000051.text: No wonder so many people come here to clear their thoughts and meditate.

136000052.text: But... never come here alone. I've heard people sometimes mysteriously and suddenly lose consciousness.

136000060.text: The Ivory Gale Haewol Quarters are situated at the highest point in Caelite Land.

136000061.text: You can see everything from up there, from the red mountains to the blue sea.

136000062.text: The relentless spirit and passion of youth as they rush headfirst towards their dream!

136000064.text: Don't forget. You look the most beautiful while you're performing the arts.

136000065.text: Must you come here? Can't you see the Hollows over there? It's dangerous!

136000066.text: When we found Caelite in this area, everyone was flabbergasted.

136000067.text: That went hand in hand with a strong sense of accomplishment, though.

136000068.text: The Ivory Gale Clan built a branch office here and even linked a cableway to it...

136000069.text: But the Sura appeared and absorbed everything and... just like that, this land was cursed.

136000070.text: Look over there! Colorful flowers are blooming and the rocks are shining like jewels.

136000071.text: It looks like the monsters are trying to lure people in using enticing colors.

136000072.text: But just like the mushrooms that are pretty on the outside but poisonous when eaten,

136000073.text: it would be better for all of us to keep our distance and enjoy from afar.

136000074.text: This isn't the place to be daydreaming. Let's head to a safer location!

136000075.text: Doesn't that look like a dragon head? It's too much of a coincidence if you ask me.

136000076.text: The spikes protruding from its back look like its ribcage.

136000077.text:
A bard sang a story about how two dragons fought,
and the loser fell from the sky and landed here...

136000078.text:
People's imaginations are amazing.
They went so far as to create another dragon for the sake of the story.

136000079.text: That rock looks like it's reaching out from the mountain. People call it Soaring Rock...

136000080.text: The rock can't possibly be alive and have grown out of the boulder, right?

136000081.text: The rock could have been tossed here and gotten stuck...

136000082.text: If I knew the answer to these questions, I would be a part of the Crystal Jungle Research team.

136000083.text: Hmm! I shall name this place Cumulus Rock! Case closed!

136000084.text: In the past, the Black Dawn appeared here and started to confront the Suwa people.

136000085.text: The chief Suwa lost his life during the battle, and to the one named Buruwar who was appointed as his successor.

136000086.text: It is said that he left a will to bury the dead in the lowlands.

136000087.text: Buruwa was famous for doing everything the other way around...\njust this time, as he would, he made a tomb in the lowlands,

136000088.text: It is said that when it rained, the tomb would be submerged and washed away. Can you hear him cry?

136000089.text: Hey! It's not because the weather is cloudy. Can't you see the smoke and ashes in front of you?

136000090.text: This isn't fog. Haze!? That's right! That's it. It's a good expression. I'll have to introduce it with it from now on!

136000091.text: Ha... So, go out there for ten li and take a look at the sky.

136000092.text: Then come back here and look up at the sky again.

136000093.text: Then you'll be like, 'Oh, that's why you call this place the Gray Sky Forest!'

136000094.text: There are terrifying predators over there. The apex of an ecosystem without natural enemies, like a king.

136000095.text: This is the best environment for them, so the numbers are growing.

136000096.text: But as a result... their prey is getting smaller and smaller.

136000097.text: From a predator’s point of view, it’s been a heartwarming story of growth so far.

136000098.text: But you'll see soon. As food runs out... the predators claw each other.

136000099.text: Shh! Be quiet. They haven't lost their hearing.

136000100.text: There were stories about people disappearing from all over the continent.

136000101.text: At first, I was mistaken for an accident or escaping...

136000102.text: Now everyone knows. They were all the work of the Black Dawn...

136000103.text: And the experiments they do on their abductees and even the dumping of failed specimens here.

136000104.text: The cracks that appear all over the world disappear soon, but some settle in one place.

136000105.text: Temporary cracks also cause damage to the ground, but they are somehow restored by nature's regenerative ability...

136000106.text: If you stay in one place, the land there will be polluted and you will die.

136000107.text: The rift has been here for a long time. It looks like it has completely lost its vitality...

136000108.text: After the rift is gone, will the land here come to life again?

136000109.text: See that big structure over there? Who made it for what?

136000110.text: A huge stake is driven in a certain direction... and chains that hang wide in all directions are installed.

136000112.text: So there must be something great down there. I'm sure! I'm not sure...

136000113.text: If you go and check it, please let me know too! Sure!

136000114.text: People who come to Red Palms Village ask how the land is even and flat here.

136000115.text: At first, I also thought that I had found a really exquisitely good land among the rugged mountains.

136000116.text: But no. It was originally a high and steep mountain, but it is said that the site was carved out of it.

136000117.text: Isn't it awesome to make a mountain flat?

136000118.text: That's why there are even jokes about whether that monster is a descendant of an engineer who was in the expedition in the past.

136000119.text: The dry oasis is not dry all year round thanks to the waterfall there.

136000120.text: In the past, the water here flowed to the extent of reaching the sea, and it is said that water was supplied to the surrounding area.

136000121.text: Now it's just a small pond... Yeah? Climate change?

136000122.text: Hmm... that may have an effect, but the most popular theory is that the water drained out due to a crack in the vicinity.

136000123.text: In the end, most of the residents and wild animals that used to live in this place have now left.

136000124.text: Imagine walking alone in a sweltering desert. Would you miss something like a cool lake?

136000125.text: In that state, you can see a hill covered with snow in front of you.

136000126.text: It's a desert, but snow? Ah~ I'm hot and tired right now, so I can see a mirage. Would you think like this?

136000127.text: But it doesn't disappear even if you keep approaching it? is this real snow? Ding! It's not snow, it's lime powder!

136000128.text: It's beautiful when it's blown by the wind... but it can be bad for you, so be careful!

136000129.text: In the Yongrin Desert, which is chronically short of water, you want to build Ereda's headquarters on the sea and rocky mountains?

136000130.text: That's crazy! How are you going to build the buildings there, and how will you get the huge amount of water for people to use? Shall I eat some sand?

136000131.text: Everyone mocked and criticized me. But Ereda did not give up.

136000132.text: Numerous scientists devoted themselves to the research, and the result of the participation of genius architects in the design.

136000133.text: He created a desalination plant with high efficiency and created the most beautiful architecture in the desert.

136000134.text: Look at those big scales. Considering the size, it would be difficult to imagine a creature other than a dragon, right?

136000135.text: Right. As you said, it may not be a scale, but a work of art that someone made secretly,

136000136.text: It may be the result of the overlapping of coincidences and coincidences in nature.

136000137.text: But if that's a dragon's scale... And if the terrain of the dragon's desert was created by the colliding of dragon's scales with the ground...

136000138.text: I think it makes me worry about the trivialities of being human because of its hugeness.
